Package: treesampler
Title: Tree-Structured Sampling from Tabular Data
Version: 0.1.0
Authors@R: person(given = "Wenzhe", family = "Huang", role = c("aut", "cre"),
                email = "51280155097@stu.ecnu.edu.cn")
Description: A stratified sampling tool that builds a hierarchical tree from
    categorical variables in tabular data and performs node-level sampling at
    each layer of the tree. Supports two sampling strategies: 'per-parent'
    (stratified within each branch) and 'level-wise' (uniform across each
    level). Designed for rapidly generating small yet representative data
    subsets for code prototyping and debugging before running analysis on full
    datasets. Includes an interactive Shiny app for visualizing the tree,
    configuring sampling parameters, and exporting reproducible R code.
Imports:
    data.tree,
    dplyr,
    shiny,
    DT,
    collapsibleTree,
    readxl,
    readr
Suggests:
    ggplot2
Depends:
    R (>= 3.5.0)
